    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-03-25T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-03-25T15:00:00-05:00" n="216"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.01/211: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-03-25T22:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 25, 1924—10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 25—8 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. By large majority Deputies today voted dethronement of Glücksburg dynasty and
                    the establishment of a republic, this latter <pb facs="0365" n="271"
                        xml:id="pg_271"/> to be confirmed by plebiscite on or about April 13th. Very
                    little enthusiasm.</p>
                <p>I am advised [Roussos?] will become Minister for Foreign Affairs at the end of
                    this week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
